net.proteusframework.processes.form.registration

Interface FormElementRegistrationFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FormElementRegistrationFactoryImpl, ScriptFormElementRegistrations

    public interface FormElementRegistrationFactory
    Defines a factory that creates FormElementRegistration at runtime based on a DataTemplate instance.
    Author:
    Pat Double (double@i2rd.com)

    • Method Detail

      • createRegistrations

        java.util.Collection<FormElementRegistration<? extends com.i2rd.componentfactory.factory.ComponentFactory>> createRegistrations(@Nullable com.i2rd.componentfactory.form.DataTemplate dataTemplate,
                                                                                                                                @Nullable com.i2rd.componentfactory.form.editor.FormEditorContext context)
        Create the registrations that are appropriate for the data template. The dataTemplate argument may be null in which case registrations that are not specific to a data template will be returned. Do not return registrations that are independent of the data template if the argument is not null. The editor context may be used if it is provided to create registrations. (It must be optional to preserve compatibility with FormEditor.hasRegistration(DataTemplate, ComponentFactory).)
        Parameters:
        dataTemplate - the data template (may be null)
        context - the editor context (may be null)
        Returns:
        collection of registrations, never null but may be empty.
